{
  "thig6.2:0.1": "Verses of the Elder Bhikkhunīs ",
  "thig6.2:0.2": "Chapter of the Sixes ",
  "thig6.2:0.3": "Verses of the Elder Vāseṭṭhi ",
  "thig6.2:1.1": "“When I lost my child I was taken over by grief; ",
  "thig6.2:1.2": "I went deranged, I lost my mind. ",
  "thig6.2:1.3": "Naked and with disheveled hair, ",
  "thig6.2:1.4": "I wandered here and there, ",
  "thig6.2:2.1": "living in middens, ",
  "thig6.2:2.2": "roadsides, and cemeteries. ",
  "thig6.2:2.3": "I wandered for three years, ",
  "thig6.2:2.4": "afflicted by hunger and thirst. ",
  "thig6.2:3.1": "When I arrived at the town of Mithilā, ",
  "thig6.2:3.2": "and I saw the one who fares well - ",
  "thig6.2:3.3": "tamer of the untamed, ",
  "thig6.2:3.4": "the self-enlightened one, fearless everywhere - ",
  "thig6.2:4.1": "I returned to sanity. ",
  "thig6.2:4.2": "I paid respects and sat down. ",
  "thig6.2:4.3": "Gotama taught me the Dhamma ",
  "thig6.2:4.4": "out of compassion. ",
  "thig6.2:5.1": "After I heard his Dhamma, ",
  "thig6.2:5.2": "I went forth into homelessness. ",
  "thig6.2:5.3": "I bound myself to the words of the Teacher; ",
  "thig6.2:5.4": "I realized the path of joy. ",
  "thig6.2:6.1": "All woes have been cut off, ",
  "thig6.2:6.2": "abandoned, finished. ",
  "thig6.2:6.3": "Now I have fully understood ",
  "thig6.2:6.4": "how grief comes into being.” ",
  "thig6.2:7.1": "The Elder Vāseṭṭhī "
}